# Host-only tooling and artifacts excluded from the Pi deploy payload.
# The deployable is the installable package: pibot/ + agent/ + pyproject.toml +
# deploy/requirements.txt. We deliberately do NOT strip host-only modules out of
# the pibot/ package (cli.py, discovery.py, provision/, connection/): agent/ imports
# transitively from pibot/, and surgically removing files would break that web for
# the sake of a few unused-on-the-Pi modules. Exclude whole top-level tooling dirs only.
.git/
tools/
tests/
docs/
firmware/
resources/
scripts/
images/
*.img
*.img.xz
releases/
.venv/
.ruff_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.pytest_cache/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
.DS_Store
PIML.md
# Host-only ML venv + the Tauri desktop app (Mission Control runs on the Mac, not the
# robot) — both are large (multi-GB) and irrelevant to the on-Pi agent.
.venv-ml/
.venv-cuda/
app/
build/
dist/
# Vendored Unity simulator (~640 MB) — host-only sim asset, never runs on the robot.
vendor/
# Scratch / tooling / docs not needed on the robot.
.hermes/
.web-research/
.github/
tmp/
.coverage
coverage.xml
htmlcov/
app_patched.py
*.mmd
CLAUDE.md
Todo.md
